    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-09-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <head>No. 1044.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Kloss</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Swiss
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-09-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 13,
                                    1887</date>. (Received September 14.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: By note of August 13
                            last, we had the honor to ask you to kindly furnish us as early as
                            possible with as precise explanations as were in your power concerning
                            the extent of the constitutional reservations made by your
                            representatives at the Paris <pb facs="0579" n="1539" xml:id="pg_1539"/>
                            Conferences of 1880 and 1883 concerning the protection of industrial
                            property.</p>
                <p>In order to inform your Department of the interpretation given to these
                            reservations in certain quarters, our Government transmits to us numbers
                            5 and 8<note n="*" xml:id="d331fn1">Inclosure not printed
                                herewith.</note> of the “Journal of the Chambers of Commerce” as
                            well as No. 7 of the “Industrial Property,” which treat of this question
                            from different stand-points.</p>
                <p>While taking the liberty to forward with this the pamphlets just
                            mentioned, we avail, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">K. Kloss.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
